[[File:1312_ACAB.jpg|thumb]]

'''A.C.A.B.'''（全寫：'''All Cops Are Bastards'''<ref>{{cite book|author1=Terry Victor|author2=Tom Dalzell|title=The Concise New Partridge Dictionary of Slang and Unconventional English|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GIuEAgAAQBAJ|year=2007|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-134-61534-6|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=GIuEAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA2 2]|access-date=2020-11-02|archive-date=2020-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200603032201/https://books.google.com/books?id=GIuEAgAAQBAJ|dead-url=no}}</ref>，中文可直譯作'''所有警察都是混蛋'''<ref>{{cite news|title=【符號學】A.C.A.B．字母縮寫紋身 想點「解」都得|url=https://www.hk01.com/第二身/292702/符號學-a-c-a-b-字母縮寫紋身-想點-解-都得|author=鄭錦儀|work=香港01|date=2019-02-09|accessdate=2020-11-02|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108023434/https://www.hk01.com/%E7%AC%AC%E4%BA%8C%E8%BA%AB/292702/%E7%AC%A6%E8%99%9F%E5%AD%B8-a-c-a-b-%E5%AD%97%E6%AF%8D%E7%B8%AE%E5%AF%AB%E7%B4%8B%E8%BA%AB-%E6%83%B3%E9%BB%9E-%E8%A7%A3-%E9%83%BD%E5%BE%97|dead-url=no}}</ref>）是一個[[首字母縮略字|首字母縮略字]]，兼[[標語|政治標語]]。部分[[持不同政见者|持不同政见者]]會用到此一政治標語，控訴自己受到[[政治迫害|政治迫害]]和[[警察暴力|警察暴力]]對待。這句流行語一般以[[塗鴉|塗鴉]]、[[刺青|刺青]]等方式書寫。它可用數字「1312」來表達——其代表每個[[英文字母|字母]]在英語中的排序。

批評者認為這個字詞是對於警察個人的侮辱，使用者應改用其他字眼去支持警隊改革<ref>{{Cite news |title=Column: Go ahead, cut the police budget. But more important, remake the LAPD |first=Steve |last=Lopez |url=https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-06-26/go-ahead-cut-the-police-budget-but-more-important-rebuild-the-lapd |access-date=2020-06-26 |website=LA Times |archive-date=2020-11-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117233452/https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-06-26/go-ahead-cut-the-police-budget-but-more-important-rebuild-the-lapd |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而支持者則認為A.C.A.B.是將警隊視作一個整體看待，沒有特地攻擊某個執法人員<ref name="GQ">{{cite web|first=Colin|last=Groundwater|title=A brief history of ACAB|url=https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/politics/article/acab-meaning|website=GQ|accessdate=2020-09-11|date=2020-06-11|archive-date=2020-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107202034/https://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/politics/article/acab-meaning|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="vice">{{cite web|first=James|last=Poulter|title=How 'ACAB' Became the Universal Anti-Police Slogan|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/akzv48/acab-all-cops-are-bastards-origin-story-protest|website=Vice|accessdate=2020-09-11|date=2020-06-08|archive-date=2020-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902053545/https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/akzv48/acab-all-cops-are-bastards-origin-story-protest|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==背景==
導演{{link-en|西德尼·海耶斯|Sidney Hayers}}於1972年的犯罪劇情片《所有警察都是……》（All Coppers Are...）中把這一短句當作標題使用。《流行語字典》（Dictionary of Catchphrases）指出，虽然纽卡斯尔的一名记者於1977年在牢房的牆壁上看到這個縮略字，但其起源可能能夠追溯至1920年代<ref>{{cite book|title=Studying the British Crime Film|first=Paul|last=Elliot|pages=78–79|year=2014|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=978-1-906-73374-2}}</ref><ref name="Partridge1986">{{cite book|first=Eric|last=Partridge|title=A Dictionary of Catch Phrases|year=1986|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-05916-9|page=1}}</ref>。

[[File:_ACAB_Montreal_Police_Car.jpg|thumb]]

英國的囚犯有時會在自己身上紋上「A.C.A.B.」——一般一隻手指紋一個字母，少數囚犯則用四個「.」代替<ref name="ThompsonBlack2006">{{cite book|first1=Tim|last1=Thompson |first2=Sue |last2=Black |title=Forensic Human Identification: An Introduction|url=https://archive.org/details/forensichumanide00thom_803|year=2006|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-8493-3954-7|page=[https://archive.org/details/forensichumanide00thom_803/page/n391 384]}}</ref>。

在德国，以A.C.A.B.攻撃某個特定人物屬刑事犯罪，以其攻擊一個群體則不算<ref name=dw>{{cite web | url = https://www.dw.com/en/german-free-speech-acab-is-a-ok-but-a-hole-is-a-no-no/a-19419352 | date = 2016-07-21 | title = German free speech: ACAB is A-OK, but A-hole is a no-no | work = Deutsche Welle | accessdate = 2020-11-02 | archive-date = 2020-05-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200523085034/https://www.dw.com/en/german-free-speech-acab-is-a-ok-but-a-hole-is-a-no-no/a-19419352 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

在某些情况下，[[反誹謗聯盟|反誹謗聯盟]]會把此一字句歸類為「仇恨符號」，並形容它為「[[光头党|光头党]]文化中一個擁有一定歷史的口號」；聯盟同時指出種族主義和反種族主義光頭黨都在使用它<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.adl.org/education/references/hate-symbols/acab |title= ACAB |author=  |date=  |website= Anti-Defamation League |accessdate= 2019-05-30 |archive-date= 2019-05-30 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190530151358/https://www.adl.org/education/references/hate-symbols/acab |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="guerra">{{cite journal | url= https://www.academia.edu/4566221 | title= Dalla strada alla letteratura, le spericolate e propizie vicende del forestierismo A.C.A.B.. Il contatto linguistico tra italiano e inglese nelle sottoculture Skinhead e Ultras | first= Nicola | last= Guerra | journal= Analele Universităţii Din Craiova, Seria Ştiinţe Filologice Linguistică Nr. 1-2 | accessdate= 2020-06-03 | publisher= Universităţii din Craiova | trans-title= From the road to literature, the reckless and auspicious events of the forestry industry A.C.A.B .. The linguistic contact between Italian and English in the Skinhead and Ultras subcultures | archive-date= 2021-10-21 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20211021175224/https://www.academia.edu/4566221 | dead-url= no }}</ref>。

==起诉记录==
[[File:ACAB_(6166309723).jpg|thumb]]）]]
在德國，當地法院把「A.C.A.B.」和「1312」都視為侮辱。在2015年，[[德国联邦宪法法院|德国联邦宪法法院]]裁定「FCK CPS」（去他媽的警察）這句只可在針對某個可識別的特定群體時視為違法。但具體個案的解釋權則交了給刑事法院<ref>{{cite news|work=The Local|date=2015-04-28|title=Constitutional Court allows 'FCK CPS' sticker|url=http://www.thelocal.de/20150428/fck-cps-high-court-agrees|accessdate=2016-08-17|archive-date=2015-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804133330/http://www.thelocal.de/20150428/fck-cps-high-court-agrees|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|author=Federal Constitutional Court|author-link=Federal Constitutional Court|date=2015-04-28|access-date=2019-02-25|title="Kollektivbeleidigung" nur bei Bezug zu einer hinreichend überschaubaren und abgegrenzten Personengruppe|url=https://www.bundesverfassungsgericht.de/SharedDocs/Pressemitteilungen/DE/2015/bvg15-023.html|language=de|archive-date=2019-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190225161909/https://www.bundesverfassungsgericht.de/SharedDocs/Pressemitteilungen/DE/2015/bvg15-023.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在[[奥地利|奥地利]]，當地法律把A.C.A.B.視為「違反公序良俗」的短語。表達者可根據行政法進行處罰，例如使用行政处罚令。有關罚款最高可达700欧元（或可選擇以拘留一周代替）<ref>³ 1 Abs. 1 Z.1 WLSG.</ref>。2019年，奥地利宪法法院裁定，在某些情况下處罰表達者將違反《欧洲人权公约》第10条——當中規定言論自由需受到一定保障。該宗案件源於一名在体育场内挥舞A.C.A.B.旗帜的足球迷。奥地利宪法法院認為该旗帜所表達的主要是「一些足球迷與警察之間的緊張關係，以及对警察這個國家管理體系的消极态度」，「沒有具體侮辱某些人物」。故此在「考虑到言论自由在民主社会中的特殊意义和功能，以及案件各個面向的情況下，有關表達應予以接受」<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.vfgh.gv.at/downloads/VfGH_Entscheidung_E_5004_2018_18.06.2019.pdf| title = Verfassungsgerichtshof, E 5004/2018-11, Rz 22 ff.| date = 2019-06-18| accessdate = 2020-11-02| archive-date = 2019-07-26| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190726165058/https://www.vfgh.gv.at/downloads/VfGH_Entscheidung_E_5004_2018_18.06.2019.pdf| dead-url = no}}</ref>。

[[File:ACAB_(All_Cats_Are_Beautiful).jpg|thumb]]
在其他欧洲国家，也有警察对表達了A.C.A.B.的人採取行動的例子。布赖恩·斯塔布福德（Brian Stableford）在2009年的《异国情缘》（Exotic Encounters）中指出「『很多年前』，寫有A.C.A.B.字樣的衬衫一度大賣。一名英国青年則因為穿上了有關的衬衫，而被控告『煽惑他人參與暴動罪』。即使他以衬衫上的『A.C.A.B.』是指『所有加拿大人都是王八蛋』（All Canadians Are Bastards）作辯解，亦無濟於事」<ref name="Stableford2009">{{cite book|first=Brian|last=Stableford|title=Exotic Encounters: Selected Reviews|year=2009|publisher=Wildside Press LLC|isbn=978-1-434-45760-8|page=26}}</ref>。2011年1月，荷兰3名[[阿贾克斯足球俱乐部|阿贾克斯]]粉絲因穿着印有数字1312的T恤而被罚款<ref name="dutchnews">{{cite news|url= http://www.dutchnews.nl/news/archives/2011/01/football_fans_fined_for_anti_p.php|title= Football fans fined for anti-police t-shirt|work= DutchNews|date= 2011-01-07|accessdate= 2016-08-17|archive-date= 2011-01-10|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110110040220/http://www.dutchnews.nl/news/archives/2011/01/football_fans_fined_for_anti_p.php|dead-url= no}}</ref>。2015年7月4日，西班牙阿利坎特一名女孩因穿着印有「A.C.A.B.」字樣的T恤而被罰款<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.yometiroalmonte.es/2015/07/04/multa-600-euros-alicante-llevar-camiseta-pone-acab/|title=Multa de 600 euros en Alicante por llevar una camiseta que pone "ACAB"|work=Yo Me Tiro Al Monte|date=2015-07-04|accessdate=2016-08-17|language=en|archive-date=2015-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705014315/http://www.yometiroalmonte.es/2015/07/04/multa-600-euros-alicante-llevar-camiseta-pone-acab/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。2016年5月22日，西班牙马德里一名34岁的女子因携带一个寫有「A.C.A.B.」和「所有的貓咪都很美麗」（All Cats Are Beautiful）的袋而被起訴<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://elpais.com/elpais/2016/05/23/inenglish/1464010258_144707.html|title=All Cats Are Beautiful or All Cops Are Bastards?|first=Jaime Rubio|last=Hancock|work=[[国家报|El País]]|date=2016-05-24|accessdate=2016-05-26|archive-date=2016-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526081552/http://elpais.com/elpais/2016/05/23/inenglish/1464010258_144707.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，3天后撤銷<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://elpais.com/elpais/2016/05/25/inenglish/1464163252_407863.html|title=Madrid police drop action against woman with All Cats Are Beautiful bag|work=[[国家报|El País]]|date=2016-05-25|accessdate=2016-05-26|archive-date=2016-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160526103208/http://elpais.com/elpais/2016/05/25/inenglish/1464163252_407863.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2017年9月15日，一名来自克罗地亚卡爾洛瓦茨的男子在他的Facebook上发布了一张照片，上面寫有「Fuck da Police A.C.A.B.」（去你媽的警察 A.C.A.B.）。他於後來因此被控告「破壞公共秩序」罪，罚款100欧元<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/karlovcanin-dobio-100-eura-kazne-jer-je-na-facebooku-napisao-acab-policija-mladica-koji-nikad-prije-nije-kaznjavan-odmah-prijavila-prekrsajnom-sudu/6965490/|title=KARLOVČANIN DOBIO 100 EURA KAZNE JER JE NA FACEBOOKU NAPISAO ACAB Policija mladića koji nikad prije nije kažnjavan odmah prijavila prekršajnom sudu|work=jutarnji.hr|date=2018-01-24|language=hr|accessdate=2018-01-26|archive-date=2018-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124113032/https://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/karlovcanin-dobio-100-eura-kazne-jer-je-na-facebooku-napisao-acab-policija-mladica-koji-nikad-prije-nije-kaznjavan-odmah-prijavila-prekrsajnom-sudu/6965490/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2019年4月4日，一名26岁的白俄羅斯冰上曲棍球迷因穿着印有「A.C.A.B.」和「1312」的T恤而被捕<ref>{{cite news |url = https://news.tut.by/society/641240.html |title = На парня из Минска составили протокол об экстремизме за четыре цифры на майке |trans-title = Youngster from Minsk detained for extremism for four numbers on T-shirt |date = 2019-06-11 |website = TUT.by |language = ru |accessdate = 2020-11-02 |archive-date = 2019-06-11 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190611225424/https://news.tut.by/society/641240.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

==其他用法==
在朋克、光头党、足球文化當中，「A.C.A.B.」可解作「eight cola eight beer」（八份可樂八份啤酒，亦即八杯可樂啤酒）。[[新納粹主義|新納粹主義者]]則把「A.C.A.B.」改成「A.J.A.B.」（全寫：All Jews are Bastards，亦即所有猶太人都是王八蛋）<ref>{{cite news | title = "A.C.A.B" beleidigt Polizistin: Vorsicht, Kopfschutz! | author = Kai Von Appen | trans-title = "A.C.A.B." insults police officer: Caution, head protection! | journal = Die Tageszeitung | date = 2013-11-04 | url = https://taz.de/ACAB-beleidigt-Polizistin/!5069609 | access-date = 2015-09-06 | archive-date = 2020-06-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200603045214/https://taz.de/ACAB-beleidigt-Polizistin/!5069609/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。[[無政府主義|無政府主義]]者有時把其背後的意思解作「Anarchist Chaotics Argue Better」（无政府主义式的混亂是更好的）<ref name = "regensburg">{{cite web | url = http://www.regensburg-digital.de/acab-ist-in-regensburg-strafbar/25012012 | title = Vorsicht: cop-ACAB-ana ist in Regensburg strafbar | trans-title = Caution: cop-ACAB-ana is punishable in Regensburg | work = Regensburg Digital | date = 2012-01-25 | access-date = 2016-02-27 | archive-date = 2020-06-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200603045232/https://www.regensburg-digital.de/acab-ist-in-regensburg-strafbar/25012012/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

其他語言亦有類似意思的短語，不過不少地區皆直接借用「A.C.A.B.」<ref name="Cameron">{{cite book |last1=Cameron |first1=Deborah |first2=Ivan |last2=Panovic |title=Working with Written Discourse |date=2014 |publisher=SAGE |page=142 |isbn=9781473904361 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PTMsAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA142 |access-date=2020-11-02 |archive-date=2021-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021175251/https://books.google.com/books?id=PTMsAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA142 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

